Idol Vs. Ideal Vs. Idle


Meanings-  Idol refers to an image representation (or a statue) of a God.
               -    Ideal refers to being perfect.
               -    Idle refers to the state of not doing anything.

Examples- The lamp was kindled before the idol of Goddess Saraswati.
                 - The idea of an ideal world seems Utopian (imaginary).
                 - Sitting idle will not lead you anywhere.
